-- South Africa Shares: Clover Industries, MTN Shares Are Active
-- B y   J a n i c e   K e w   a n d   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 2012-06-05T11:16:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-05/south-africa-shares-clover-industries-mtn-shares-are-active.html
The FTSE/JSE  Africa  All Share Index
rose for the first time in three days, advancing less than 0.1
percent to 33,093.11 by 12:52 p.m. in Johannesburg.  The following are among the most active equities in the
market today. Stock symbols follow company names.       Clover Industries Ltd. (CLR)  , South Africa’s biggest
dairy company, headed for its biggest gain in almost two months,
climbing 2.2 percent to 13.70 rand. The company renewed an
outsourcing agreement with Eqstra Flexifleet (Pty) Ltd., saying
it will help it reduce costs and increase volume over time.  MTN Group Ltd. (MTN)  , Africa’s biggest mobile-phone
company, fell for the first time in four days, dropping 0.4
percent to 135.51 rand. The  Democratic Alliance , South Africa’s
main opposition party, said that the Hawks, an elite police
unit, are probing allegations of corruption related to the
company’s Iranian unit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
